data.name: wordGiveIntro.Text
data.value: Using the Word Giveaway will allow you to either input a certain word, or have the Subathon Tool generate a random word for you. Once this has done, you then have options to specify what happens when a viewer gets the word correct. Does it choose the first person to type the word as the winner? Or do all of the users to enter the specified word get entered into a random draw?

data.name: randomNumGenIntro.Text
data.value: Using this tool, viewers will be able to guess a number in the chat, and can keep going until someone guesses right. Optionally, you can set cooldowns, so users can only guess once in a row. (i.e. after one person has guessed, they can't guess again until someone else does, or after 2 minutes.)

data.name: bitsStoreIntro.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the Bits Store! This is a new store where you can buy different items for your viewers, every time they cheer! It's currently in early beta, but don't forget to give it a go, and let us know how it goes! Since viewers can't buy the items themselves through this, the streamer (you) buy it for them. It's a more fun way of keeping track of how much they've cheered in one stream*.
* IMPORTANT NOTE: Currently, the amount cheered is ONLY stored while the program is running. If it crashes, or if you close the software, the amount cheered is lost, and everyone will start at 0. I'm looking into changing this once it leaves Beta.

data.name: label18.Text
data.value: An important note: This feature is currently top priority for the Subathon Tool. Currently, it isn't integrated yet, but the setting is here for testing purposes. Once it's ready, you'll be the first to know.

data.name: label28.Text
data.value:
If enabled, every time you open the Subathon Tool, it will check if there's 10 or more log files currently in the AppData folder. To save on storage and memory resources, it will ask whether you want the Subathon Tool to clear this folder out. You'll have the option to "Export" specific files if you don't want to lose a certain one.
This feature won't start working until after the next restart, if currently disabled.

data.name: staffPowerOutline.Text
data.value:
By enabling this feature, The Mad Gamers' staff will be able to help you during Subathons. They can't edit your preferences or start/stop the countdown timer. This feature only allows them to add time manually for donations/subs/resubs/bits if they don't trigger automatically.
The access they have via this command may change, but we'll always let you know in plenty of time of any changes.
